5.3 Macro Geometry Angles (Future Use)

Î˜ (Theta): macro-cycle phase angle

Î¦ (Phi): liquidity-momentum phase angle

These will be defined once the full wave/oscillation model is integrated.

6. Leading / Lagging Treatment

VCF interprets metrics based on their temporal behavior:

Leading: Yield curve, credit spreads, equities momentum

Coincident: GDP, CPI

Lagging: Unemployment

The engine uses this for:

Weighting

Phase dampening

Cycle prediction

Stress indexing

7. Numerical Stability Requirements

To ensure consistent cross-regime behavior:

Always use np.clip() on normalized values

Use np.arctan2() instead of arctan() for angles

Run checks for NaN or infinite values

Use rolling windows for long-term metrics (e.g., CPI)

8. Output Format

The engine should output:

date
x1_norm
x2_norm
...
x7_norm
magnitude
theta
phi
stress_index (future)

9. Versioning

This is v1.0, the first stable mathematical spec.
Future spec versions will add:

Harmonic resonance

Curvature of economic trajectories

Vector field divergence

Liquidity harmonics

MVSS integration

